def: To any extent; in any degree; at all.You are not to go loose any longer. Shak.Before you go any farther. Steele.
A modified form of Buddhism which prevails in Thibet, Mongolia,and some adjacent parts of Asia; -- so called from the name of itspriests. See 2d Lama.
A South American rodent (Cavia rupestris), allied to the Guineapig, but larger; -- called also rock cavy.
Extreme hatred or detestation; the feeling of utter dislike.
To throw out of the proper orbit; to unsphere. Shak.
A bird or other animal having slender toes. [Written alsolepodactyle.]
To take into the hand; to take up; to help. [Obs.] Wyclif.Spenser.
The extreme end of the chancel or choir; properly the round orpolygonal part.
